CatDescriptText: Dr. Roy T. Anderson, dentist, 2015 Centre Avenue, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 29, 1959, pg. A1 with question: Do you believe the state and city FEPC laws are helping Negroes to get jobs they never held before?" answer reads: "Being a native of Pittsburgh and the State of Pennsylvania, I believe the state and city FEPC laws have made great strides in making the Negro a first-class citizen."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Dr. Roy T. Anderson wearing light colored short sleeved smock, standing in dentist office, 2015 Centre Avenue
